{
  "id": 5459864205393920,
  "name": "CSS border-shape",
  "summary": "CSS border-shape enables creating non-rectangular borders, with any arbitrary shape (polygon, circle, shape(), etc).\r\n\r\nThough border-shape accepts the same shapes as clip-path, it is fundamentally different: border-shape defines the shape of the border, decorates it, and clips only the inside. \r\n\r\nborder-shape has two variants: one variant that strokes a shape, and another variant that fills between two shapes.",
